{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"toefl-sentences","unitId":"sentence-011","title":"Sentence 11","sectionId":"sentences-011","sectionTitle":"Sentence 11-20","pageStart":83,"pageEnd":89,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":42,"duplicateEntryCount":4,"pages":[{"number":83,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Sentence 11"},{"type":"text","text":"Most substance contract when they freeze so that the density of a"},{"type":"text","text":"substance’s solid is higher than the density of its liquid."},{"type":"text","text":"大多数物质冻结时会收缩，所以它们的密度在固态时高于液态"},{"type":"text","text":"时。"},{"type":"section","text":"语法笔记"},{"type":"text","text":"本句的主干是Most substance contract，句中when引导的从句作其时"},{"type":"text","text":"间状语。so that引导整个句子的结果状语从句。"},{"type":"section","text":"核心词表"},{"type":"entry","text":"contract /ˈkɑːntrækt/ vi. 收缩；订合同","headword":"contract"},{"type":"note","text":"同义 shrink v. 收缩"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 contraction n. 收缩；压缩"},{"type":"entry","text":"freeze /friːz/ v. （使）结冰，（使）凝固","headword":"freeze"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 freeze over 被冰覆盖；冰封"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 freezer n. 冰柜"},{"type":"entry","text":"density /ˈdensəti/ n. 密度","headword":"density"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 atmospheric density 大气密度"}]},{"number":84,"blocks":[{"type":"note","text":"同根 dense a. 稠密的"},{"type":"entry","text":"solid /ˈsɑːlɪd/ n. 固体 a. 固体的","headword":"solid"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 solid mass 实体"},{"type":"text","text":"solid particle 固体微粒"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 solidify v. 凝固"},{"type":"text","text":"solidly ad. 牢固地"},{"type":"entry","text":"liquid /ˈlɪkwɪd/ n. 液体 a. 液体的","headword":"liquid"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 liquid crystal 液晶"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 liquefy v. （使）液化"},{"type":"text","text":"liquidize vt. 把…榨成"},{"type":"section","text":"主题归纳"},{"type":"text","text":"与“力学”相关的词："},{"type":"entry","text":"action /ˈækʃn/ n. 作用力","headword":"action"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 mutual action 相互作用"},{"type":"entry","text":"dynamics /daɪˈnæmɪks/ n. 动力学","headwor